Lay the coals not too hot, so that the heat shall not be too fiery and seize on the stiff-necked fellow’s face and get into the depths of his breast. Get up on to the pyre they have laid for you, lie down on the bed you deserve3 and then, if you like, argue that my god of fire is nothing.'’ ’
